I fixed the bug, although don&#39;t remember exactly how. Here are some of the things I did, ordered by level of importance (the most likely answer it at the top).


**1. Configure your `packagingOptions`**
----------------------------------

Go to your `android/app/build.gradle` and add the following snippet of code at the end of your `android {...}`:

    android {
    
        // Some stuff...
    
        packagingOptions {
            exclude &#39;META-INF/services/javax.annotation.processing.Processor&#39;
        }
    
    }


**2. Check `buildTypes`**
---------------------

Once again, in your `android/app/build.gradle`, at `android {...}`, you should have a `buildscript {...}` inside. If not, add it. If added, revise it has the same values for the following properties (`packagingOptions` from the first point added):

    android {
    
        // Some stuff...
    
        buildTypes {
            release {
                minifyEnabled true
                shrinkResources true
                signingConfig signingConfigs.release
            }
        }
    
        packagingOptions {
            exclude &#39;META-INF/services/javax.annotation.processing.Processor&#39;
        }
    
    }


**3. Update multidex**
------------------

Inside of your `android/app/build.gradle` as well, update the multidex you have at `dependencies {...}`. It&#39;d also be great to update any other implementation you have there, but the important one is multidex. This is mine:

    dependencies {
        implementation &quot;org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-jdk7:$kotlin_version&quot;
        implementation &quot;androidx.multidex:multidex:2.0.1&quot;
    }

If you don&#39;t have `dependencies {...}` in your file, add it at the end.


**4. Another dependencies upgrade**
-------------------------------

This time it&#39;s in the other gradle file. The route is `android/build.gradle`, and you just have to enter in the `buildscript {...}` and update what you find in `dependencies {...}`. In my case:

    buildscript {

        // Some stuff...
    
        dependencies {
            classpath &quot;com.android.tools.build:gradle:7.1.2&quot;
            classpath &quot;org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-gradle-plugin:$kotlin_version&quot;
